definition: a proud stiff pompous gait, to walk with a lofty proud gait, often in an attempt to impress others
details:
noun
- a proud stiff pompous gait
= synonyms: swagger, prance
- brace consisting of a bar or rod used to resist longitudinal compression
verb

= example: to walk with a lofty proud gait, often in an attempt to impress others
